<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>National map — real estate monitor</title>
<script src="assets/plotly.min.js"></script>
<style>
  body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
         color:#1b1f23; margin:0; line-height:1.45; }
  .wrap { max-width:1180px; margin:0 auto; padding:24px 18px 60px; }
  h1 { font-size:1.7rem; margin:6px 0 4px; }
  .sub { color:#5b6670; font-size:.9rem; margin:4px 0; }
  a { color:#1f5fa8; }
  .chart { border:1px solid #d9dee3; border-radius:6px; padding:4px; margin:12px 0; }
  .note { background:#fff8e6; border:1px solid #f0d98c; border-radius:6px;
          padding:10px 13px; font-size:.85rem; color:#5b4a00; margin:10px 0; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">
  <p><a href="index.html">← Back to your dashboard</a></p>
  <h1>National county map</h1>
  <p class="sub">Every US county, color-coded by the metric you pick. Use the
     <strong>dropdown at the top-left of the map</strong> to switch metrics; hover a
     county for its value; scroll to zoom. Your tracked counties are
     <strong>outlined in black</strong>. Generated {{ generated }}.</p>

  <div class="chart">{{ chart | safe }}</div>

  <div class="note">
    Public data, not a forecast. Gray counties have no public value for the
    selected metric. Coverage: home value {{ coverage.home_value }}/{{ coverage.total }}
    counties, rent {{ coverage.rent }} (Zillow publishes county rent only where
    listing volume supports it), income {{ coverage.income }}. Sources: Zillow
    ZHVI/ZORI (county) and Census ACS 5-year.
  </div>
  <p class="sub">Outlined markets: {{ tracked | join(', ') }}.</p>
</div>
</body>
</html>
